# Claude Agent System

This project has a multi-agent assessment framework in `.claude/`.

## Structure
- `.claude/agents/` - Agent definitions (role, scope, checklist)
- `.claude/commands/` - Executable prompts (assessment + operational)
- `.claude/hooks/` - Lifecycle hooks (session-start, protect-sensitive, etc.)
- `.claude/rules/` - Domain-specific coding rules (security, testing, typescript, nextjs, infrastructure)
- `.claude/state/` - Persistent orchestrator state (gitignored)
- `.claude/reports/` - Generated assessment output (gitignored)
- `.claude/settings.json` - Permissions, hooks, and env config

## Root Files
- `CLAUDE.md` - Project context for AI sessions
- `AGENTS.md` - Agent system documentation
- `AGENT_TEAMS.md` - Team-based agent organization
- `AGENT_BACKLOG.md` - Prioritized action items from latest assessment

## Usage

### Assessment Commands
- To run an individual agent: read the command file and follow its instructions
- To run all agents: read `.claude/commands/assess-all.md` and use subagents for parallelism
- Reports go to `.claude/reports/` - never commit these

### Operational Commands
- `healthcheck` - Quick project health snapshot
- `fix` - Fix highest-priority issues from latest assessment
- `discover` - Scan codebase and update orchestrator state
- `deploy` - Pre-deployment verification checklist
- `review-pr` - Review a PR against project standards
- `security-audit` - Focused security scan

## When the user says "assess" or "audit"
1. Check if they want a specific domain (CI/CD, infra, testing, etc.)
2. Read the corresponding command from `.claude/commands/`
3. Follow the instructions exactly
4. Write output to `.claude/reports/`

## When making code changes
1. Read the relevant rules from `.claude/rules/` before coding
2. Follow security rules for auth, secrets, and validation
3. Follow TypeScript rules for type safety
4. Follow testing rules for test structure and coverage

## Agent IDs
- 00: Orchestrator (master coordinator)
- 01: CI/CD
- 02: Infrastructure
- 03: Testing
- 04: API/Functions
- 05: Database
- 06: UI Layer
- 07: Architecture
- 08: Refactoring (SOLID/DRY)
- 09: Bugs & Features
- 10: Vertical Feature Completeness
